<section id="fullbio">
	<h2>Official Bragging Bio</h2>
	<p>
	Originally a professional musician and circus clown, Derek Sivers created CD&nbsp;Baby in 1998.
	</p><p>
	It became the largest seller of independent music online, with <a href="/done">$100M in sales for 150,000 musicians</a>.
	</p><p>
	In 2008, Derek <a href="/trust">sold CD Baby for $22M</a>, giving the proceeds to a charitable trust for music education.
	</p><p>
	He is a frequent <a href="http://www.ted.com/speakers/derek_sivers.html">speaker at the TED Conference</a>, with over 5 million views of his talks.
	</p><p>
	In 2011, he moved to Singapore and <a href="/a">published a book</a> which shot to #1 on all of its Amazon categories.
	</p><p>
	His new company is <a href="http://woodegg.com/">Wood Egg</a>, publishing annual guides to 16 countries in Asia.
	</p>
</section>

